@BecomingDataSci As far as programming / data analysis experience, I took an intro to C in my 5th year undergrad (I have one year where Calc 2 wiped me out), and then learned MatLab during my PhD.

Self-taught #rstats during my PostDoc.

@walkingrandomly @StatsForBios I actually stopped using MatLab, even when it was available, due to the hassle of installing and keeping contact w/ license server, and how hard it is for others to make use of my ideas.

Started learning #rstats 11 years ago, haven't looked back.

@walkingrandomly @StatsForBios I hear you. 

I spent my entire PhD learning MatLab, even got to the point of learning to program GUIs.

I'm in bioinformatics / metabolomics, and all the fun stats toys are in #rstats.

The day I figured out how to properly plot in ggplot2 was an epiphany.

Take a break from teaching...  #AcademicLife As an inexperienced lecturer who just started my second year, I currently teach #rstats to > 300 students. Markings have been automated, so that I have bandwidths to develop new and creative materials for https://t.co/XtcwumkbO9 .

My gh actions for auto grading workflow:
* httr::GET() submissions from Canvas
* waldo::compare() #rstats objs
* magick::image_compare() plots
* praise::praise() if correct
* rmarkdown::render() feedback
* gmailr::gm_send_message() to students
